comments: For me, the words that had letters similar to the English alphabet made it easier to remember those words. The words with the "A" like letter were the easiest for me to recognize. Some of the letters looked like the cyrillic alphabet and the tiny, tiny bit of Russian that I know kind of helped there. I think once I realized that the 4 words that I was shown would *not* necessarily be the word, I was tested on, it made the task easier. I focused then on trying to remember the word/image rather than simply trying to see which word would possibly come up.
